content:
You asked, we listened. In order for a parameter to appear in your Messaging for Web auto-response URL, you must add one or more placeholders to your URL and configure a corresponding Web Page Parameter in the Messaging Component.

Where: This change applies to Messaging for Web. View required editions.

How: Add one or more placeholders to your URL configuration. For each placeholder, create a corresponding Web Page Parameter. To insert end user values from the client into the placeholder, continue to use Auto-Response API. If you have an existing Auto-Response component with a URL that used parameters, we recommend updating your configuration in the Messaging Component builder.

SEE ALSO
Personalize the URL for your Auto-Response Component
title: Preventing Unwanted Parameters in Auto-Response URLs
